description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for a transformation in your career pathway and want to work for an ‘Outstanding’ mental health trust as rated by the CQC, then look no further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community Mental Health Services for Older People are looking for a full-time Occupational Therapist to join our community team at Colne House, Watford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome compassionate and innovative team players. You will work beyond your core OT skills to provide occupation focused care for older people with complex mental health and physical needs in a community setting. The role involves working collaboratively within the multidisciplinary team and outside agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Occupational Therapist in HPFT you would:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be part of an OT team, not a lone professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be part of an MDT that values and respects OT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be able to use your initiative and creative skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop knowledge and application of the Model of Human Occupation and other specialist assessments (cognitive, sensory, OT outcome measure based on EKOS).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefit from 5% high cost of living allowance, up to maximum of £1791&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would receive support and be part of a network across all the older people’s mental health OT services. You will be part of a developing and expanding OT service. You will have access to varied and relevant continuous development opportunities, as well as a host of staff networks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Car driver essential (unless you have a disability as defined by the Equality Act 2010 which prevents you from driving)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At HPFT we also welcome; Return to Practice OT&#39;s with paid opportunities, students working whilst studying, and part-time flexible hour working hours can be considered,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details /informal visits please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name, Amanda Stratford Job title, Head Occupational Therapist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address, amanda.stratford1@nhs.net Telephone number, 07775546850&lt;/p&gt;
